{"TopicId":77401,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Amazing U2 cockpit video","CreatedByName":"PlonioFludrasco","CreatedById":98915,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-07-12T19:26:54Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"PlonioFludrasco","CreatedById":98915,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-07-12T19:26:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/q48Swb2ATww?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cbr\u003EJust amazing!!\u003Cbr\u003EEDIT: Note the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.google.it/url?sa=t\u0026amp;rct=j\u0026amp;q=\u0026amp;esrc=s\u0026amp;source=web\u0026amp;cd=1\u0026amp;ved=0CCIQFjAA\u0026amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fjalopnik.com%2F5537629%2Fthe-140-mph-chase-cars-of-the-us-air-force\u0026amp;ei=14zBU_7CEYGy7AbS54Bo\u0026amp;usg=AFQjCNFpzpUtp7S0HWIIBcYky6X4DObD7Q\u0026amp;bvm=bv.70810081,d.ZGU\u0026amp;cad=rja\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Echasing car\u003C/a\u003E at the end!!\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222014-07-12T19:32:09Z\u0022 title=\u002207/12/2014 07:32  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 12, 2014\u003C/time\u003E by PlonioFludrasco\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"montyben101","CreatedById":74173,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-07-12T19:33:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWait, at the end was that a car following a plane!!??\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex_NL","CreatedById":58254,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-07-12T19:37:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThe chase car is standard procedure during U2 landings. The chase car is driven by a veteran U2 pilot.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELanding a U2 is extremely difficult, the chase car pilot is literally talking the U2 pilot to the ground.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TechnicalK3rbal","CreatedById":86903,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-07-12T19:46:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EA U2 only has to wheels, not counting those on the wings, which have to be tilted in that direction for them to contact the ground. So you basically have to stop and then just let the plane tilt to either side.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEdit: which is why it\u0027s extremely difficult to land.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222014-07-12T22:49:33Z\u0022 title=\u002207/12/2014 10:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 12, 2014\u003C/time\u003E by TechnicalK3rbal\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"78stonewobble","CreatedById":97559,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-07-13T08:56:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWell it is basically a giant powered glider after all. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHow long does it take to get to full altitude, it\u0027s got a relatively small engine doesn\u0027t it?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rickenbacker","CreatedById":2349,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-07-14T13:59:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EProbably takes a while, but look at that ground roll on takeoff! It\u0027s got a pretty powerful engine for its weight, I think. Definitely one of the most powerful motorgliders around!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGreat video, I especially liked when you could see the speed on the left side, and it read 105 kts / mach 0.7!\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}